All Classes

  • Class Description
    Date
    This class represents a date and includes methods that checks if the user-input date is valid and compares if a current date is before, equal to, or after another date
    International
    This class contains information about international students and if they are study abroad or not.
    Main
    Main class that starts the GUI program.
    Major
    This method contains all values for majors.
    NonResident
    This class extends Student and contains operations and data that are specific to nonresidents.
    Profile
    This class defines a Profile that is to be used by Student.
    Resident
    This class is the superclass Resident and contains the profile and the credit hours that the student is taking and also has an operation for financial aid.
    Roster
    Container class defines the array list data structure to hold the student roster.
    Student
    This class is the superclass Student and contains the profile and the credit hours that the student is taking.
    Tristate
    This class contains information about tri-state students including the state that they live in (NY or CT) and gives them a discounted tuition rate.
    TuitionManagerController
    This class is the client driver class that takes in user-inputted information and does functions with them using the Roster class
